 x^5+5x+6= (x^3-x)(x^2+1)+6x+6. 
 6x+6 \equiv 0 \,\,\,\text{in}\,\,\,\mathbb Z_n[x].  
{\rm mod}\ x^2\!+1\!:\,\ x^2\equiv -1\,\Rightarrow\, \color{#c00}{x^4\equiv 1}\,\Rightarrow\, \left\{\!\begin{eqnarray} f = x\color{#c00}{x^4}\!+5x+6\\ \equiv\, \color{#0a0}{6x+6}\end{eqnarray}\right\}\,\ 
\,\ x^2\!+1\mid f\! \iff\! x^2\!+1\mid \color{#0a0}{6(x+1)}
